The Gauteng Transport Department is dedicating 70 percent of all booking slots to driving licence renewals. eNCA JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Transport said it is dedicating 70 percent of all booking slots to driving licenses renewals. The announcement was made by MEC Jacob Mamabolo. READ: Motorists call for online licence renewals to be scrapped This is to address the current backlogs. Mamabolo held a meeting with the Road Traffic Management Corporation as well as members of the Mayoral Committees in all municipalities. READ: Drivers' Licence Backlog: Mamabolo admits there is a problem He admitted there was a problem with allocating slots for driving licence renewals. He's warned that Driver Testing Licensing Centre managers who undermine this directive will be dealt with harshly and face possible suspension.